    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @Spone \r\n\r\nI came up with a solution to your problem. Indeed now InstantSearch.js relies on the `search` event to update the URL, and in your code you are preventing the search from happening. But there is a way to do that in the [following jsFiddle](https://jsfiddle.net/bobylito/e2jd75oL/1/).\r\n\r\nWhat I did is change the implementation of the searchFunction to have this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  searchFunction: function(helper) {\r\n    var searchResults = $('#movies');\r\n    if (helper.state.query === '') {\r\n      movies.helper.once('result', function() {\r\n        searchResults.hide();\r\n      })\r\n    }\r\n    helper.search();\r\n    searchResults.show();\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn this case, there will be a search but as soon as the results come back it hides the content of the hits.\r\n\r\nAs for cleaning the URL completely, instantsearch.js is not able to do that as of now.",
